cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Memory-Centric Clinical LLM — Capacity over TFLOPS"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Balkeum Labs"
abstract: >-
  A reproducible single-machine harness demonstrating that a large clinical LLM
  (27B, INT4) can be hosted on a consumer CPU using system RAM where a mid-range
  consumer GPU runs out of VRAM. Self-adapting across AMD/Intel hosts, it measures
  RAM-fit vs GPU-OOM capacity, inference throughput/TTFT, energy (tokens-per-joule),
  and federated LoRA-adapter bandwidth savings, using synthetic FHIR-shaped data and
  open Gemma-2 stand-ins for MedGemma.
keywords:
  - federated-learning
  - large-language-models
  - edge-ai
  - clinical-nlp
  - quantization
  - llama.cpp
license: MIT
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-11"
